FBIS4-58966 "drnes090_j_94021" FBIS-NES-94-090 Daily Report 10 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Salih Appoints Al-'Attar Acting Prime Minister Salih Appoints Al-'Attar Acting Prime Minister JN1005055094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 0430 GMT 10 May 94 JN1005055094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Presidential Council Decree No. 12 issued on 9 May -- read by announcer] [Text] The chairman of the Presidential Council, cognizant of the Constitution of the Republic of Yemen; in view of the dismissal of Prime Minister Engineer Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas', and in view of the requirements of public interest and after the approval of the President Council, decrees the following: Article I. Dr. Muhammad Sa'id al-'Attar, deputy prime minister, will be charged with the duties of the prime minister. Article II. This decree will be valid as of date of issue and will be published in the official gazette. Issued at the Presidency in Sanaa on 29 Dhu al-Qi'dah, 1414 of the hegira, 9 May 1994. [Signed] Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the President Council
